{
  "text": "To explain the experimental data, it is essential to understand the driving force for the precipitation of salts. Typical precipitation reactions are driven by the concentration of lattice ions, pH, temperature and the thermodynamic ion activity product of the species. [CITATION_1] In our system, the precipitation temperature and pH are equal for all species. Then we need to consider the concentrations of lattice ions and the thermodynamic products.",
